# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldMage2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "As Sarah woke to the next day, she found Samayra still asleep."
    new "As Sarah woke to the next day, she found Samayra still asleep."

    old "In their sleep, Samayra had twisted herself round and round, until eventually ending up resting her head on Sarah's chest."
    new "In their sleep, Samayra had twisted herself round and round, until eventually ending up resting her head on Sarah's chest."

    old "Sarah didn't object."
    new "Sarah didn't object."

    old "After a short while, she carefully sneaked out of the bed, leaving Samayra to sleep by herself."
    new "After a short while, she carefully sneaked out of the bed, leaving Samayra to sleep by herself."

    old "Sarah woke to the nex day."
    new "Sarah woke to the nex day."

    old "The house made no sound."
    new "The house made no sound."

    old "It felt to Sarah as if the silent and empty house judged her, a witness to her crimes."
    new "It felt to Sarah as if the silent and empty house judged her, a witness to her crimes."

    old "Too awake to stay in bed, Sarah got up."
    new "Too awake to stay in bed, Sarah got up."

    old "Arriving in the main study room, Sarah slowly let her eyes glide across it."
    new "Arriving in the main study room, Sarah slowly let her eyes glide across it."

    old "The same."
    new "The same."

    old "Everything was exactly as they had left it when they set out for Bagrad."
    new "Everything was exactly as they had left it when they set out for Bagrad."

    old "The many books. The collection of artifacts. Even Xan's training instructions were still resting where they had been put down."
    new "The many books. The collection of artifacts. Even Xan's training instructions were still resting where they had been put down."

    old "Sarah's eyes fell on Xan's desk."
    new "Sarah's eyes fell on Xan's desk."

    old "Xan had a habit of drifting around the house. She would find him reading in the oddest of places."
    new "Xan had a habit of drifting around the house. She would find him reading in the oddest of places."

    old "But this room, and this desk, this had been the center of his studies, and with it, the center of his world."
    new "But this room, and this desk, this had been the center of his studies, and with it, the center of his world."

    old "Sarah had managed to find her own alcoves and rooms in the house, but this room was where they had spend most of their time together."
    new "Sarah had managed to find her own alcoves and rooms in the house, but this room was where they had spend most of their time together."

    old "She sighed heavily."
    new "She sighed heavily."

    old "Perhaps, Sarah thought, if she had hated Xan all this would have been easier."
    new "Perhaps, Sarah thought, if she had hated Xan all this would have been easier."

    old "But she owed him too much to hate him. And so instead, the guilt lingered. The guilt of what she had done to buy herself her freedom."
    new "But she owed him too much to hate him. And so instead, the guilt lingered. The guilt of what she had done to buy herself her freedom."

    old "Sarah wandered over towards the desk."
    new "Sarah wandered over towards the desk."

    old "Sitting down in Xan's chair, she looked over the many papers and books that were piled up."
    new "Sitting down in Xan's chair, she looked over the many papers and books that were piled up."

    old "It looked like a mess, but Sarah had seen him work enough to know there was a method to his madness."
    new "It looked like a mess, but Sarah had seen him work enough to know there was a method to his madness."

    old "Staring out at it now, the pile of documents just seemed like madness."
    new "Staring out at it now, the pile of documents just seemed like madness."

    old "She carefully lifted one piece of paper from the pile and read the title of the document."
    new "She carefully lifted one piece of paper from the pile and read the title of the document."

    old "'A preliminary Analysis on Snow Crystal as an Alchemical Catalyst.'"
    new "'A preliminary Analysis on Snow Crystal as an Alchemical Catalyst.'"

    old "Sarah carefully put the piece of paper back where she had found it. Alchemical research was the last thing she was interested in at the moment."
    new "Sarah carefully put the piece of paper back where she had found it. Alchemical research was the last thing she was interested in at the moment."

    old "Off to the side, coming from the window, Sarah could see movement."
    new "Off to the side, coming from the window, Sarah could see movement."

    old "Getting back up, she walked up towards the window and stared out."
    new "Getting back up, she walked up towards the window and stared out."

    old "Outside, Lethram went on as it always had. A bustling of commerce."
    new "Outside, Lethram went on as it always had. A bustling of commerce."

    old "The house sat upon one of the intersections connecting the wealthier port district with the poorer hill districts."
    new "The house sat upon one of the intersections connecting the wealthier port district with the poorer hill districts."

    old "As a result, one could see just about every facet of the city play out from this window."
    new "As a result, one could see just about every facet of the city play out from this window."

    old "Seeing the city that was as close to her as a home, it oddly soothed her."
    new "Seeing the city that was as close to her as a home, it oddly soothed her."

    old "Yet she was also happy to be inside."
    new "Yet she was also happy to be inside."

    old "A degree of seperation between herself and the real world, now again full of uncertainty."
    new "A degree of seperation between herself and the real world, now again full of uncertainty."

    old "For years, her only mantra had been to listen to Xan and follow his lessons. Now there was nobody to tell her what to do."
    new "For years, her only mantra had been to listen to Xan and follow his lessons. Now there was nobody to tell her what to do."

    old "Sarah knew she wasn't the weak girl from the alley anymore, but she also knew her power, great as it was, could not protect her from everything."
    new "Sarah knew she wasn't the weak girl from the alley anymore, but she also knew her power, great as it was, could not protect her from everything."

    old "Fading into existence from seemingly nowhere, the spirit manifested itself."
    new "Fading into existence from seemingly nowhere, the spirit manifested itself."

    old "The blank mask that passed for a face sat upon his inky, black body as it twisted and swirled."
    new "The blank mask that passed for a face sat upon his inky, black body as it twisted and swirled."

    old "After having carried the fate stone through the house, the spirit was now untethered from its flask."
    new "After having carried the fate stone through the house, the spirit was now untethered from its flask."

    old "Whatever it was worth, it seemed to enjoy its new found freedom."
    new "Whatever it was worth, it seemed to enjoy its new found freedom."

    old "You seem full of worry."
    new "You seem full of worry."

    old "Sarah kept staring out the window."
    new "Sarah kept staring out the window."

    old "I have a lot to worry about."
    new "I have a lot to worry about."

    old "I imagined you would have taken more favorably to your new freedom."
    new "I imagined you would have taken more favorably to your new freedom."

    old "What we did to Xan..."
    new "What we did to Xan..."

    old "The spirit rushed forward."
    new "The spirit rushed forward."

    old "Do not concern yourself with the fate of that mage."
    new "Do not concern yourself with the fate of that mage."

    old "He received not a fraction of what was due to him, consider it mercy."
    new "He received not a fraction of what was due to him, consider it mercy."

    old "Sarah laughed humorlessly."
    new "Sarah laughed humorlessly."

    old "Mercy? We killed him."
    new "Mercy? We killed him."

    old "For a moment, the spirit was quiet, only observing her. Then it spoke."
    new "For a moment, the spirit was quiet, only observing her. Then it spoke."

    old "So, is that what we must do now, Sarah?"
    new "So, is that what we must do now, Sarah?"

    old "Must we now perform the sad faces and the spilling of tears, so that we might imagine our conscience clean?"
    new "Must we now perform the sad faces and the spilling of tears, so that we might imagine our conscience clean?"

    old "The spirit reached out with his tendrils, shaped as claws, seizing her by the shoulders."
    new "The spirit reached out with his tendrils, shaped as claws, seizing her by the shoulders."

    old "I will make no apologies for seeking to rid myself of his horrid presence."
    new "I will make no apologies for seeking to rid myself of his horrid presence."

    old "Nor should you make apologies for your part in securing your own freedom."
    new "Nor should you make apologies for your part in securing your own freedom."

    old "Sarah shook her body."
    new "Sarah shook her body."

    old "Let go of me, Razaphel."
    new "Let go of me, Razaphel."

    old "The spirit obliged, slinking back towards its corner."
    new "The spirit obliged, slinking back towards its corner."

    old "I imagine you might enjoy-"
    new "I imagine you might enjoy-"

    old "You imagined wrong. I'm in no mood for anything, least of all that."
    new "You imagined wrong. I'm in no mood for anything, least of all that."

    old "Or perhaps the girl is now the object of your pleasures?"
    new "Or perhaps the girl is now the object of your pleasures?"

    old "Jealous, are we now?"
    new "Jealous, are we now?"

    old "Go ahead, mourn that wicked man, your mentor..."
    new "Go ahead, mourn that wicked man, your mentor..."

    old "But if you want, I shall tell you tales of what he did to me."
    new "But if you want, I shall tell you tales of what he did to me."

    old "His many tortures, seeking to draw out from me my secrets. I wonder, would you think of him the same if you knew?"
    new "His many tortures, seeking to draw out from me my secrets. I wonder, would you think of him the same if you knew?"

    old "Sarah waved her hand, dismissing him."
    new "Sarah waved her hand, dismissing him."

    old "I don't have any illusions about him, but I do owe him for all he taught me."
    new "I don't have any illusions about him, but I do owe him for all he taught me."

    old "Without him, I'd still be what I was...lost, powerless."
    new "Without him, I'd still be what I was...lost, powerless."

    old "Slowly, the spirit emerged back from his corner, drawing closer."
    new "Slowly, the spirit emerged back from his corner, drawing closer."

    old "Tell me, child of starlight..."
    new "Tell me, child of starlight..."

    old "For what reason have you taken his blood on your hands? What did you hope to gain?"
    new "For what reason have you taken his blood on your hands? What did you hope to gain?"

    old "Power"
    new "Power"

    old "For a moment, Sarah considered the words of the spirit."
    new "For a moment, Sarah considered the words of the spirit."

    old "What did she want. Why had she done what she had done."
    new "What did she want. Why had she done what she had done."

    old "But the answer was obvious to her."
    new "But the answer was obvious to her."

    old "Power."
    new "Power."

    old "A hissing sound emerged from the creature, the closest it could produce to a laugh."
    new "A hissing sound emerged from the creature, the closest it could produce to a laugh."

    old "A most surprising answer."
    new "A most surprising answer."

    old "Sarah turned to face Razaphel."
    new "Sarah turned to face Razaphel."

    old "Surprising? How?"
    new "Surprising? How?"

    old "I have come across those who are delirious with lust for power."
    new "I have come across those who are delirious with lust for power."

    old "They are more often a simple kind, with simple pleasures."
    new "They are more often a simple kind, with simple pleasures."

    old "I imagined you more complex."
    new "I imagined you more complex."

    old "I only gave you the truth. I had no desire to impress you, spirit."
    new "I only gave you the truth. I had no desire to impress you, spirit."

    old "Freedom"
    new "Freedom"

    old "Freedom."
    new "Freedom."

    old "I suspected as much."
    new "I suspected as much."

    old "You thought that would be my answer."
    new "You thought that would be my answer."

    old "Ever since you came to this place, I could see it in your eyes."
    new "Ever since you came to this place, I could see it in your eyes."

    old "This magic, it was but a tool for you. A tool to secure your real ambition, to live on your own accord."
    new "This magic, it was but a tool for you. A tool to secure your real ambition, to live on your own accord."

    old "It's the truth."
    new "It's the truth."

    old "Even before I lost everything, I can now see that my life was being dictated by others."
    new "Even before I lost everything, I can now see that my life was being dictated by others."

    old "So when Xan threatend to take what little freedom I had managed to procure, away..."
    new "So when Xan threatend to take what little freedom I had managed to procure, away..."

    old "You had to act."
    new "You had to act."

    old "I understand, child."
    new "I understand, child."

    old "Sarah sighed deeply and turned back to looking across the room."
    new "Sarah sighed deeply and turned back to looking across the room."

    old "Now what..."
    new "Now what..."

    old "You want me to answer that for you?"
    new "You want me to answer that for you?"

    old "I just...I need to understand what my place is now."
    new "I just...I need to understand what my place is now."

    old "I freed myself from Xan but..."
    new "I freed myself from Xan but..."

    old "You are free to do as you wish, but you fear that you do not yet know what that is..."
    new "You are free to do as you wish, but you fear that you do not yet know what that is..."

    old "I need to better understand my circumstances. My position."
    new "I need to better understand my circumstances. My position."

    old "Should you wish council, I am available."
    new "Should you wish council, I am available."

    old "Sarah smiled at the spirit."
    new "Sarah smiled at the spirit."

    old "The truth was that she hardly knew what to make of Razaphel, alien as he was."
    new "The truth was that she hardly knew what to make of Razaphel, alien as he was."

    old "But she also knew that there were not many people left that could understand her. And Sarah wasn't even sure Razaphel was people."
    new "But she also knew that there were not many people left that could understand her. And Sarah wasn't even sure Razaphel was people."

    old "Let me ponder it myself for a while."
    new "Let me ponder it myself for a while."

    old "The spirit swirled, animated."
    new "The spirit swirled, animated."

    old "Go, child, and enjoy your new found freedom."
    new "Go, child, and enjoy your new found freedom."

    old "With that, the spirit vanished same as it had appeared."
    new "With that, the spirit vanished same as it had appeared."

    old "Sarah turned back towards the window, continuing to observe the movements of the city."
    new "Sarah turned back towards the window, continuing to observe the movements of the city."

    old "What now, she wondered half in awe, half in fear."
    new "What now, she wondered half in awe, half in fear."

    old "The answer did not come to her. Not yet."
    new "The answer did not come to her. Not yet."

